{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> ψῐθῠρ-ίζω</b>, <br /> <i>Doric dialect</i> <b>ψῐθῠρ-ίσδω</b>: (ψίθυρος):— <b>whisper,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Gorgias” 485e; πρός τινα [prev. author] “Euthd.” 276d, 4th-3rd c.BC: Duris Epigrammaticus 69J.; ἀλλήλοις 3rd c.BC: Theocritus Poeta Bucolicus 27.68. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__2</b></Level3> <b>whisper what one dares not speak out, whisper slanders,</b> κατά τινος [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.AD: Alciphro Epistolographus 3.58, LXX.Psa.40(41).7; ψ. και᾽ διαβάλλειν 4th c.AD: Themistius Sophista “Orationes” 21.262c \">LXX+4th c.AD+</a>]:—<i>passive</i>, τὸ ψιθυριζόμενον ὄνομα [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus “Alcibiades” 23. \">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__3</b></Level3> <i>metaphorically</i> of trees, <b>whisper</b> (i. e. <b>rustle</b>), ὁπόταν πλάτανος πτελέᾳ ψιθυρίζῃ [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Nubes” 1008 (_anapaest meter_)\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; also of swallows, <b>twitter,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD(?): Pollianus Epigrammaticus 5.90. \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]","strongNumber":"G9794","accentedUnicode":"ψιθυρίζω","shortDef":"to whisper","mediumDef":"to whisper","stepGloss":"to whisper","stepTransliteration":"psithurizō","_step_Type":"verb"}]}